  rows:
    - [ziplongest_name_eq,
       zip_longest.__name__.__eq__,
       ["zip_longest"],
       true,
       "itertools.zip_longest.__name__.__eq__('zip_longest') == True — zip_longest is a C-implemented iterator class in Modules/itertoolsmodule.c that aggregates elements from multiple iterables, filling short iterables with a fillvalue (default None) rather than stopping at the shortest; its __name__ is 'zip_longest'; str.__eq__('zip_longest') returns True; new to extra182"]
    - [ziplongest_name_len_11,
